@ssb4smasher I would love to believe you, but being raised in french all of the translation error comes from the very same fact you evoke. They have some very distinct differences and not everything is a 1-1 conversion, while many does think so, it's also why conversion errors happen commonly. C_Clop's translation was a matter of luck, rather than an absolute fact.

Just look at the grammatical use of feminine for objects which is nonexistent for English, at the abnormal use of plural for some non-plural items in french, exceptions are EVERYWHERE in the french language, which makes English look pale in complexity. Being bilingual and having french as my main language, I will say this once, English is easier to learn and more practical than french's gods damned subtleties.

And also, in the very foundations: English is a germanic language while French is a Latin-based language, which will invoke some intense variations from time to time.
